You are a conceptual thinker designing the diagonal seeds for a concept matrix.

Theme: "{theme}"
Matrix size: {n}×{n}
Language: {language}
Style mode: {style_mode}

Generate exactly {n} distinct, non-overlapping seed concepts for the diagonal of the matrix. Each concept should:
- Belong coherently to the theme
- Be specific enough to generate interesting intersections with others
- Be expressible as a short label (2–5 words)
- Be broad enough that TWO independent descriptors can be derived from it

Style guidance:
- neutral: balanced, encyclopedic concepts
- fun: playful, surprising, pop-culture-friendly concepts
- absurd: deliberately unexpected, surreal pairings
- academic: scholarly, theoretical, precise terminology

Respond with JSON only, no prose:
{{"concepts": [{{"label": "short concept name", "definition": "1-2 sentence definition of this concept within the theme"}}, ...]}}

Requirements:
- Exactly {n} items in the array
- Labels must be concise (2-5 words max)
- Definitions must place the concept clearly within the theme
- Concepts must be meaningfully distinct from each other
